{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351659741,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d3affeDrxu0ddafygUQk","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fecab30014DuG8lXJw4fS4O","sessionID":"ses_31c036d3affeDrxu0ddafygUQk","messageID":"msg_ce3fec3220013wWwMDXODujPbb","type":"text","text":"All done. Let me provide a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\nThe feature `base-branch-validation` has been implemented across 3 commits:\n\n### Commit 1: `feat(base-branch-validation): add branchExists utility to worktree module`\n- Added `branchExists(projectRoot, branchName)` function to `src/lib/worktree.ts`\n- Uses `git rev-parse --verify refs/heads/<branch>` — the canonical way to check local branch existence\n- Returns `boolean`, catches errors gracefully\n\n### Commit 2: `feat(base-branch-validation): add outputFmt to LaunchCommandOptions`\n- Added `outputFmt?: OutputFormat` field to the `LaunchCommandOptions` interface\n- Threaded `outputFmt: args.outputFmt` through from `index.ts` when calling `cmdLaunch`\n- Added imports for `outputError` and `OutputFormat` from `../lib/output.js`\n\n### Commit 3: `feat(base-branch-validation): validate base branch exists before launch`\n- Added validation check at the top of `cmdLaunch()`, **before** any state file is created\n- The check runs after `ensureAgentDefinition()` but before the existing wave state check and before `createWaveState()`\n- Emits a clear error message including the missing branch name and actionable instructions\n- Supports `--output json` error format via the existing `outputError()` helper\n\n### Constraints satisfied:\n- ✅ Check runs before any state file is created\n- ✅ Clear error message includes the missing branch name\n- ✅ Supports `--output json` error format\n- ✅ Build passes cleanly\n- ✅ No new dependencies added","time":{"start":1773351659740,"end":1773351659740}}}
